				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Okay so you are thinking of the mage class well it is a fine choice for battle and magic. The mage is a special class being able to summon powerful elements to help in battle is a far greater ability then trying to cast without one. Here is what the pets do for each spell of the pet:4lvl pets are the weakest of them but when you get your hands on it it feels great.WATER:Better Ac,Normal Attack,Normal Hp--FIRE:Low Hp,More dmg per turn WIND:Normal Attack,Normal Hp,Can go invis:Okay now that is out of the way I have found that the water is the most affective this is new info the pets also cast minor spells now. Once you hit lvl8 get ready the pets get better they get the ability to Double Attack,Parry,and Bash.Those skill will help you alot taking on creatures will feel alot easier. Okay I cant cover all the pet lvls but at lvl12+ your pets gain the ability to attack magical creatures like ghouls and wisps.Okay now at the begining you will fell very weak once you hit 4 it gets better and better what can I say I have a lvl35 Mage you have the ability to summon food,water,staffs all you need for combat so your melee skills will die as you find your magic better the that staff you are limited to armor,which is cloth but you will have many spells to offset this as your mage grows you will fell more powerful then most classes in my mind you can gain exp faster and attack better then any wiz wich would be worrying if that root would work you dont you just tell your pet to attack and cast away.Word of the wise take some dmg do not let your pet take all the dmg or you could lose him and then death is not far.Good Luck to you and I hope this will help you clear your mind about Mages. Elemetal:Power is the key to a mage once the conjure begins all other will flee in terror of what you are about to bring to life.
